 Middle Ages it was a center for the manufacture of cloth, including the famous ‘Lincoln green’.","African American: adoption of the surname in 1 above, in honor of Abraham Lincoln, the 16th president of the US, who abolished slavery.","History: Abraham Lincoln (1809–65), 16th president of the US, was the son of an illiterate laborer, descended from Samuel Lincoln, who had emigrated from England to MA in 1637."],"variants":[{"name":"Linkins","meanings":["English: variant of <b>Linkin</b>, which itself is a form of   Lincoln  , prevalent in Kent."]},{"name":"Lindsay","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Lindsey in Lincolnshire, England. This is first found in the form <i>Lindissi</i>, apparently a derivative of the British name of   Lincoln  . To this was later added the Old English element <i>ēg</i> ‘island’, since the place was virtually cut off by the surrounding fenland. The surname was taken to Scotland at an early date and is the name of an important and powerful Scottish family.","Irish: adopted as an equivalent ofvarious Gaelic names (see   Lindsey  )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":17,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":30,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":39,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":84,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Burghersh Lincoln was born in 1298, in Northamptonshire, England. She had at least 2 sons with Henry Burghersh Bishop Lincoln."},"et":{"1298–":"1298–Surnud","1292–1340":"1292–1340","1318–1357":"1318–1357","1320–1348":"1320–1348","1298–Female":"1298–Surnud","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1292":"1292","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1357":"1357","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","1320":"1320","11 Jun 1320":"11. juuni 1320","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Lincoln, Badby, Northamptonshire, England":"Badby, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Badby, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Badby, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1298–":"1298–Kuollut","1292–1340":"1292–1340","1318–1357":"1318–1357","1320–1348":"1320–1348","1298–Female":"1298–Kuollut","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1292":"1292","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1357":"1357","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","1320":"1320","11 Jun 1320":"11. kesäkuuta 1320","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Lincoln, Badby, Northamptonshire, England":"Badby, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Badby, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Badby, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1298–":"1298–Décédée","1292–1340":"1292–1340","1318